-- Colombia Stock Movers: Banco Davivienda, Avianca, Canacol Energy
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-05-15T22:03:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/colombia-stock-movers-canacol-energy-avianca-taca-holding.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  dropped 0.7 percent to 14,581.17, while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  decreased 0.4 percent to 1,733.67.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA)  , the owner of
Colombia’s biggest airline, gained 3.3 percent to 3,790 pesos.
Avianca Taca said consolidated first-quarter profit rose 41
percent from the prior year to 62.8 billion pesos ($35 million),
according to a regulatory filing yesterday.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based oil
company that operates fields in Colombia, was unchanged at 1,240
pesos after earlier rising as much as 2 percent. Net income for
the fiscal third quarter ended March 31 was $3.7 million
compared with a net loss of $852,000 in the year-earlier period,
according to a regulatory filing. Production averaged 13,163
barrels of oil per day compared with 9,958 the prior year,
according to the filing.  Banco Davivienda SA (PFDAVVND)  , Colombia’s third-biggest
bank, gained 0.3 percent to 20,940 pesos. Standard & Poor’s
changed its outlook on Banco Davivienda’s BBB- credit rating to
stable from CreditWatch negative. The bank’s planned acquisition
of HSBC Holdings Plc’s units in  Costa Rica , El Salvador and
Honduras had triggered the negative outlook.  To contact the reporter on this story:
